---
// Sekcja Writing — artykuły dwujęzyczne (PL + EN) jako dowód eksperckości.
---
<section id="writing" class="relative overflow-hidden bg-background dark:bg-[var(--c-page)] text-dark dark:text-[var(--c-ink)] px-8 md:px-16 py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-dark/10 dark:border-[var(--c-line)] transition-colors duration-500">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -top-[10%] -left-[8%] w-[58%] h-[78%] rounded-full blur-[130px] opacity-[0.14] dark:opacity-[0.48]" style="background: radial-gradient(circle, #B07A4E 0%, transparent 70%)"></div>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto relative z-10">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] opacity-60 mb-6">
      <span class="text-[#B07A4E]">—</span> 06 · Writing
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-4xl md:text-6xl tracking-[-0.03em] uppercase leading-[0.95] mb-8">
      I write about AI<br />for business<span class="text-accent">.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1.4fr_1fr] gap-10 items-start">
      <p class="font-sans text-base leading-relaxed opacity-80 max-w-xl">
        Plain-language articles in Polish and English on AI agents, automation, RAG and data —
        from how a document agent plans its own steps to what the data says about AI adoption in
        Poland vs the EU. Written for business owners and recruiters, not just engineers.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
        <a
          href="/artykuly/"
          data-art-pl="/artykuly/"
          data-art-en="/en/articles/"
          class="inline-block text-center px-8 py-4 rounded-[2rem] bg-dark dark:bg-accent text-primary dark:text-dark font-sans font-bold text-base hover:bg-accent dark:hover:bg-primary hover:scale-[1.02] transition-all duration-300 no-underline"
        >
          Browse articles →
        </a>
        <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-center opacity-50 uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">Polish &amp; English</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
